ascism, the public spectacle of the Olympic Games would be an ideal setting for propaganda efforts.\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3237, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3110, \"end\": 3117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_O'Duffy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.039375637528187e-64, \"text\": \"O'Duffy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_O'Duffy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_O'Duffy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fascism\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3144}, {\"ngram\": \"the public spectacle\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3166}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3170, \"to\": 3187}, {\"ngram\": \"an ideal setting\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3213}, {\"ngram\": \"propaganda efforts\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3236}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WhenBerlin hosted the Olympic Games in 1936, the Nazi governmentusedsports as part of its drive to strengthen the \\\"Germanic race,\\\" to exercise political control over its citizens, and to prepare German youth for war.\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3287, \"end\": 3291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"score\": 0.9996884961160091, \"rank\": 0.00024719470891008727, \"text\": \"Nazi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\"}, {\"begin\": 3353, \"end\": 3366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nordic_race\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Germanic race\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nordic_race\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nordic_race\"}, {\"begin\": 3433, \"end\": 3439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999988799970102, \"rank\": 1.1170840532873734e-06, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WhenBerlin\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3248}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3273}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3320}, {\"ngram\": \"its drive\", \"from\": 3324, \"to\": 3333}, {\"ngram\": \"political control\", \"from\": 3381, \"to\": 3398}, {\"ngram\": \"its citizens\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3416}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 3450, \"to\": 3453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While not as drastic as Hitler's ideals, O'Duffy did share similar sentiments in using sport \\\"be able to keep pace with other countries\\\".\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3480, \"end\": 3486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8489910121947173e-21, \"text\": \"Hitler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\"}, {\"begin\": 3497, \"end\": 3504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_O'Duffy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.039375637528187e-64, \"text\": \"O'Duffy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_O'Duffy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eoin_O'Duffy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"similar sentiments\", \"from\": 3515, \"to\": 3533}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3548}, {\"ngram\": \"pace\", \"from\": 3566, \"to\": 3570}, {\"ngram\": \"other countries\", \"from\": 3576, \"to\": 3591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He suggested that funds from theIrish Hospital Sweepstakes- a lottery that contributed millions to building hospitals - should be redirected towards restoring the health of the unfit.\", \"from\": 3594, \"to\": 3777, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"funds\", \"from\": 3612, \"to\": 3617}, {\"ngram\": \"theIrish Hospital Sweepstakes-\", \"from\": 362