r\", \"from\": 5895, \"to\": 5911}, {\"ngram\": \"his remaining prestige\", \"from\": 5929, \"to\": 5951}, {\"ngram\": \"an abortive effort\", \"from\": 5955, \"to\": 5973}, {\"ngram\": \"the Spanish Civil War\", \"from\": 5995, \"to\": 6016}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, Tokyo were announced as hosts of the1940 Olympics.\", \"from\": 6019, \"to\": 6081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6031, \"end\": 6036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999995668064031, \"rank\": 4.327499251680213e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 6022, \"to\": 6029}, {\"ngram\": \"hosts\", \"from\": 6055, \"to\": 6060}, {\"ngram\": \"the1940 Olympics\", \"from\": 6064, \"to\": 6080}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During their bid, Japanese diplomatslobbiedforeign governments to persuade their Olympic committees to withdraw the candidacies of their cities from the race.\", \"from\": 6082, \"to\": 6240, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their bid\", \"from\": 6089, \"to\": 6098}, {\"ngram\": \"their Olympic committees\", \"from\": 6157, \"to\": 6181}, {\"ngram\": \"the candidacies\", \"from\": 6194, \"to\": 6209}, {\"ngram\": \"their cities\", \"from\": 6213, \"to\": 6225}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 6231, \"to\": 6239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is evidence that representatives from Italy and Great Britain were approached but no mention of Ireland, possibly because they were never really considered a serious contender for hosting this mega event.\", \"from\": 6241, \"to\": 6451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6285, \"end\": 6290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"score\": 0.9998239244740539, \"rank\": 0.00017610653408712648, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"w